rComments: Professor Hoeschele is one of the best professors I've had during my 3 years at U of T. She is extremely knowledgeable, a very engaging lecturer, and a fair marker. I had her for two classes last semester, and loved them both. She's accessible outside class, and her lectures are well organized and super interesting. Can't recommend her enough!

Her class Women in Antiquity has almost nothing to do with women in antiquity. Lots of reading of ancient texts. No assignments, only two midterms and a final exam. these evaluations are terribly made, the terms to identify dont have anything to do with women in antiquity, same with the quotes you have to explain and also remember the author.
